title: Low-emission vehicles eligible for a plug-in grant

heading_context: Low-emission vehicles eligible for a plug-in grant
chunks.html_content:
Some types of low-emission vehicles are eligible for a grant from the government, so that you can buy them more cheaply.

You do not apply for the grant. The seller includes it as a discount in the purchase price.
chunks.plain_content:
Low-emission vehicles eligible for a plug-in grant
Some types of low-emission vehicles are eligible for a grant from the government, so that you can buy them more cheaply.
You do not apply for the grant. The seller includes it as a discount in the purchase price.

heading_context: Low-emission vehicles eligible for a plug-in grant
chunks.html_content: If you work for a vehicle dealership or manufacturer, you can apply for a grant using the online portal.
chunks.plain_content:
Low-emission vehicles eligible for a plug-in grant
If you work for a vehicle dealership or manufacturer, you can apply for a grant using the online portal.

heading_context: Low-emission vehicles eligible for a plug-in grant
Eligible vehicles
chunks.html_content:
Only vehicles that have been approved by the government are eligible.

The discount you can get depends on the type of vehicle.

The types of eligible vehicles are:

  • wheelchair accessible vehicles
  • motorcycles and mopeds
  • small and large vans
  • small and large trucks
  • taxis

heading_context: Low-emission vehicles eligible for a plug-in grant
chunks.html_content:
Some wheelchair accessible vehicles can be sold at a 35% discount. The seller will include the discount in the purchase price.

The maximum discount is £2,500.

heading_context: Low-emission vehicles eligible for a plug-in grant
chunks.html_content: If you work for a vehicle dealership or manufacturer, you can apply for a grant using the online portal. There are a limited number of grants - you should find out how many are available before you apply.
chunks.plain_content:
Low-emission vehicles eligible for a plug-in grant
If you work for a vehicle dealership or manufacturer, you can apply for a grant using the online portal. There are a limited number of grants - you should find out how many are available before you apply.

heading_context: Low-emission vehicles eligible for a plug-in grant
chunks.html_content:
To be eligible for a grant, the vehicle must:

  • be converted from a passenger vehicle (sometimes known as a ‘category M1 vehicle’)
  • have zero tailpipe CO2 emissions
  • be able to travel at least 112km (70 miles) without any emissions
  • cost less than £35,000 (recommended retail price, including VAT and delivery fees, not including cost of conversion)

The vehicles that can be converted are:

  • Citroen e-Berlingo
  • Citroen e-Spacetourer Business M
  • Citroen e-Spacetourer Business XL
  • Nissan e-NV200 Combi (5 seater)
  • Nissan e-NV200 Combi (7 seater)
  • Peugeot e-Rifter
  • Vauxhall Vivaro-e Life - Combi

heading_context: Low-emission vehicles eligible for a plug-in grant
Small trucks
chunks.html_content:
The maximum discount available for some small trucks is £16,000.

These vehicles are sometimes called N2 vehicles.

To be eligible for a grant, the vehicle must:

  • be between 4,250kg and 12,000kg gross weight
  • have CO2 emissions of at least 50% less than the equivalent conventional Euro VI vehicle that can carry the same capacity
  • be able to travel at least 96km (60 miles) without any emissions

The eligible vehicles are:

  • FUSO eCanter
  • Iveco eDaily
  • Magtec MEV75 (Incomplete)
  • Paneltex Z75
  • Tevva T7 – T133 (Incomplete)
